BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 5.295 of the Revised Code be 5
enacted to read as follows: 6
Sec. 5.295. The fourth day of February is designated as 7
"John Rankin Day," in honor of the American abolitionist, 8
minister, and educator who was born that day in 1793. Settling 9
in Ripley, Ohio, in 1822, he was an early anti-slavery writer, a 10
conductor on the underground railroad, and a major contributor 11
to Ohio's legacy of freedom. 12
Section 2. Notwithstanding any contrary provision in 13
section 105.41 of the Revised Code or in any rule or procedure 14
adopted by the Capitol Square Review and Advisory Board, the 15
Board shall designate, not later than October 1, 2025, a 16
prominent place on the lawn or other outside grounds of Capitol 17

